# Button Usage

Default `<Button>` has no background (border only). Use it for standard actions.

For primary (filled) actions, use `<Button variant="primary">`.

For secondary actions, use `default`, `outline`, `secondary`, or `ghost` (all no-fill by default).

Never add local color classes to buttons (`text-blue-*`, `bg-blue-*`, `border-blue-*`, `text-indigo-*`, `bg-sky-*`, etc.).

Do not invent custom visual variants for new pages; use existing `ui/button` variants tied to theme tokens.
